Package ca.queensu.cs.cisc124.notes.generics.basics

Interface Stack<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements in this stack
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayStack, LinkedStack, ListStack
    public interface Stack<E>
    The Stack interface represents a last-in-first-out (LIFO) stack of elements. In addition to the usual push and pop methods, this interface allows the user to get the number of elements in a stack and to query if the stack is empty.
